<br>
One could address it many ways the monk tanking ability.  I'd address it only one way.<br>
In PoP make the following additions to mob damage<br>
<br>
The following is for all mobs in PoP lvl 52+<br>
If warrior +0 damage when pc hit.<br>
If paladin/shadow knight +10 points of damage per hit.<br>
If ranger/rogue +25 points of damage per hit.<br>
If cleric/bard +40 points of damager per hit<br>
If monk/beast lord +45 points of damage per hit.<br>
If shaman +50 points of damager per hit.<br>
If druid+ +60points of damage per hit<br>
<br>
If wizard/enchanter/necro/mage +75points of damage per hit.<br>
<br>
This allows there to be a clear choice in grabbing a tank.  It also allows monks to be unusable as tanks.  Monks were never supposed to be tanks but I will not support a dirrect nerf to rebalance the game.<br>
<br>
As for the taunt issue some less skilled warriors have complained about.<br>
<br>
Warriors have complained they can't aggro mobs above their level.  last time I checked almost all exp grinds are done on blues.  If you aren't 60 you aren't leading raids on even conned or higher mobs.  This complaint in my view is class envy.<br>
<br>
Warriors have stated concerns about holding aggro better in groups.  If their aggro ability is increased as much as most have asked for the game will brake.  <br>
<br>
What is a resenable fix I'd support a class type aa ability that gave you a 40% chance to get an insint double taunt when you press the taunt button.  This is the most I'd give.  Why?  because taunt is barely an issue and PoP will release better taunting weapons.<br>
<br>
Odd thing is I've seen warriors roll on higher damageing lesser aggroing weapons when there is a ranger or rogue who could use it.  That's akin to a paladin asking for a hate generateing weapon over any warriors present.<br>
<br>
Sorry this is as polite as I get.  The idea though is valid if you can read pass my manorisms (sp)?<br>
<br>
Remember you still are the best damage absorber when compared to sk/pal so that small dif in damage per hit will add up n stack well with your current abilities.  Just don't forget to support paladins getting ToK and DS fixed while you try and get these issues addressed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukeryath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keryath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/7/02 1:08:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1056.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fixing the warriors in PoP and addressing taunt concerns</span><hr size=1> I'd suggest:<br>
