<br>
I don't want to be the best tank because I have the best abilities.  I want to be the best tank because I play better then the next guy.  Can any of you guys say the same?  <br>
<br>
How was the pal/sk/war orginaly attended to be?<br>
<br>
The warrior was to be a solid tank with easy ability to play.  It's still the easiest class to play in general.<br>
<br>
The sk and paladin were ment to be lesser tanks if they didn't use mana or know how to use their spells.  However if they did know how to play with their spells and mana they could be as good as a warrior and if they were exceptionaly talented they'd be better then the warrior.  This is where reputation used to be the make or break point.  &lt;-- this is currently where we are at in traditional groups as soon as those in traditional groups figure it out the better eq will be.  <br>
