<br>
Its simple why warriors need to be re-balanced:<br>
<br>
We were balanced in with the all other melee classes in SoV era based upon our superior armor and how much melee power and class abilities we had vs the lesser armors, different melee powers and class powers they had.<br>
<br>
Now we no longer have the best gear, instead the same gear is shared by most if not all of the other classes. Warriors lost nothing directly here, however the other classes became as powerful as a warrior in this point.<br>
<br>
The hybrid classes, sans bards, have received the full force of the caster balance without suffering any drawbacks to the melee side of their powers. The healing hybrid classes have also received part of the priest balance as to date. <br>
<br>
So yes the other classes did receive more. Now it is time to give warriors something to restore the balance, the only question left is what. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uthehavocblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TheHavocblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 328<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/8/02 9:10:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1056.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.guardianalliance.org/cgi-bin/upload/Tha.gif h=30 w=20></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fixing the warriors in PoP and addressing taunt concerns</span><hr size=1> This has been gone over ever so many times.  Can we please kick the dead horse again?  Maybe it'll come back to life, so we can kill it again.<br>
